<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Woolley knows her son had problems beyond EverQuest, and she tried to get him help by contacting a mental health program and trying to get him to live in a group home...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> There's good parenting for you. If your child has problems, send him away to a home. That'll cure him! Elizabeth Woolley, where were you when Shawn was playing 12 hours a day when, like you said, &quot;wasn't supposed to because he was epileptic, and the game would cause seizures...&quot;?<br>
